  <h1>Making Presentations</h1>

  <img src="/presentations.png" alt="Making Presentations" style="width: 100%; max-width: 600px; margin: 1.5rem auto; display: block;" />

  <p>
    A scientific presentation is not a paper you read aloud. It is a <strong>performance</strong> — a curated,
    time-constrained experience designed to leave your audience with one clear idea they did not have before.
    The slides are props. You are the presenter. This guide covers how to make both work together.
  </p>

